Jyothi Laldas Stanger Hospital team receiving an award for the first position in the Best Performing Pediatric Unit. Photo: supplied Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories THE Stanger Regional Hospital scooped three prestigious awards in the recent MEC’s Annual Service Awards held last Friday at the Durban ICC. The annual awards ceremony, seeks to recognise performance excellence in the delivery of health services to the citizens of the province.     The health employees were recognised across numerous genres that make up the health system.      The awards were run in three segments, covering Special Recognition, Special Awards and Entry and Desktop. Stanger
   Hospital
  was one of the institutions recognised for best performance in KwaZulu-Natal and received awards for Best Performing Pediatric Unit - Regional Hospitals (first place), Best Performance for Financial Management (fourth place) and Most Improvement in Reduction of Maternal Mortality Rate over the last three years. The Stanger Hospital management and staff were honored to be rewarded for their hard work.        24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  